Frequently Asked Questions

 How much car insurance coverage do I need?



There are a number of factors that help determine how much car insurance you may need, like how far you drive, the type of vehicle you own, where you live and your budget. Consider the following when thinking about what auto insurance coverage options are best for you:

If you’re making car payments, chances are the lender will require the vehicle to have comprehensive and collision coverage.
The deductible determines how much you pay out-of-pocket after a covered loss. So, if you’re looking to save money, consider increasing your deductible, which will lower your auto insurance rate. 
The age of your vehicle is another factor. If you have an older vehicle with a lower value, it might not make sense to pay for more expensive coverage like comprehensive and collision.
You should also consider how much liability coverage you need. Remember, if you only have $30,000 in liability coverage and you cause an accident that generates $100,000 in damages then you could be liable for the amount above your coverage limit. 

Taking these and other factors into consideration will put you on a path  to better understand how much car insurance you might need. Learn what each  coverage term means so you can craft the right coverage plan for your  needs, or speak with one  of our knowledgeable agents. They’ll help create a customized plan specifically  tailored to your needs. 




 By law, how much car insurance am I required to have?



Many states require drivers to have liability insurance in order to make  driving financially safe for all. If you don’t have the required amount of  insurance, you may be subject to fines and possible suspension or even loss of your  driver’s license. Find out how much insurance your state requires. You can also speak with one of our local agents, who can tell  you exactly how much insurance you need.




 How can I lower my auto insurance premium?



Everybody loves to save money, and auto insurance is no exception, so we’ve provided a few things you should consider when shopping for the best deal. 

Vehicle Make and Model: The type of vehicle you drive can have a big impact on your rate. For example, a BMW will typically cost more than a Ford. 
Anti-Theft Devices: You can generally get discounts for anti-theft features installed in your vehicle, because if your vehicle is harder to steal then the risk of loss is lower and that could save you money. 
Location, Location, Location: Where the vehicle is parked at night and how much you drive can have an impact on your rates, because if you drive 40 miles to work then there is a higher risk that you could get into a collision. 
Driving Record: The fewer accidents and tickets you have on your record, the lower your rate will be. 
Grades in school.
Bundle and Save: When you bundle auto and home coverage you could save on both your auto and home insurance.

A Mercury agent can help find discounts for which you may qualify, and offer other money-saving tips to help you save even more. 











