					Full Description



Mercury General Corporation, incorporated on January 20, 1961, is an insurance holding company. As of December 31, 2016, the Company and its subsidiaries were primarily engaged in writing personal automobile insurance through 14 insurance subsidiaries in 11 states, principally California. The Company's segments include Property and Casualty Lines, and Other Lines. The Company also writes homeowners, commercial automobile, commercial property, mechanical breakdown and umbrella insurance. The Company's insurance policies are sold through independent agents receiving a commission for selling policies. As of December 31, 2016, the Company sold its policies through approximately 9,700 independent agents, its owned insurance agencies, Auto Insurance Specialists LLC (AIS) and PoliSeek AIS Insurance Solutions, Inc. (PoliSeek), and directly through Internet sales portals.The Company's Property and Casualty business segment offers various insurance products to the Company's individual customers and small business customers. These insurance products include private passenger automobile, which is the Company's primary business, and related insurance products, such as homeowners, commercial automobile and commercial property. The insurance products consisting the Property and Casualty business segment are sold through the same distribution channels, through independent and owned insurance agents, and go through underwriting process. The Company's Other business segment offers automobile mechanical breakdown warranties, which are primarily sold through automobile dealerships and credit unions. The Company's subsidiaries include Mercury Casualty Company, American Mercury Insurance Company, Mercury County Mutual Insurance Company, Mercury Insurance Company of Georgia, Workmen's Auto Insurance Company, Mercury Select Management Company, Inc., AIS and Fannette Funding LLC.

» Full Overview of MCY







